user_review: This place was amazing!  In Montreal for a business trip, we decided to go with a recommendation from a coworker. Each of us ordered a meal however the plates are big enough to share!
Food was good but the owner ripped me off. My dinner for one person ended up being $95 !!!!  It was not that good!
One word... Amazing! The food is authentic home cooking. The Chef was very accommodating and recommended fantastic dishes.

We were lucky enough to be staying around the corner from this little gem on an evening when all of the bistros in the area were packed. Charming ambience.  The gentlemen waiting on us were gracious, helpful and unobtrusive. Everything we ate was delicious from the brik to the couscous dish with lamb, prunes and raisins.  I'm pretty sure the baklava is the best I've ever eaten.  Highly recommend for a quiet, delicious meal in a charming setting.

It was my first time trying out the moroccan food, and everything was delicious! Especially, Chicken Tagine were very soft and had a nice scent of lemon. With couscous, it was a perfect combo! But we ordered a bit too much and it was over priced. Make sure you only order 1 platter for 2.

We had got dinner to go twice while staying in the neighborhood and loved it. The couscous aux legumes was a delicious vegetarian option. On top of that the owner threw in a spinach dish with sauce that I can only describe as magic. For our next order he packed us a box of things we ordered as well as things we did not - including a tureen of that magic sauce which we put on everything. He is so generous and friendly!

We were looking for Moroccan food in Montreal and found this on Trip Advisor. The food was as good as myMother in law used to cook. We started with the artichoke and hearts of palm salad which was so fresh and tasteful. Casserole d'escargot was prepared to perfection. Harira soup was so proficiently spiced with a great consistency.  The tajine of chicken with lemon and olives was delicious. The couscous was so light and airy The couscous  royal has packed with lamb chops, chicken, lamb shank, and merguez which was exceptional. To full to finish it all, but finished dinner with mint tea. This is definitely the best Moroccan food I have eaten since my mother in law passed.
A bit expensive but the couscous was great and the owner threw in some freebies that were much appreciated
In the center of quebecs food capital. I'm shocked it's still open after all there years. I went once because I lived 1 block away. I still live one block away. I never went back.
